      "message": "I\u0027m not sure we need the first fStagingBuffer array that just holds ownership and nothing else.\n\nWhat I was thinking is we have three arrays here:\n\n// Theses are buffers currently not in use by anyway (current frame or GPU).\nstd::vector\u003cstd::unique_ptr\u003cGrSB\u003e\u003e fAvaiableStagingBuffers;\n\n// These are buffers owned by the current \"frame\". They will be used on the GPU when we submit this frame.\nstd::vector\u003cstd::unique_ptr\u003cGrSB\u003e\u003e fActiveStagingBuffers;\n\n// These are buffers currently in use on the GPU\nstd::vector\u003cstd::unique_ptr\u003cGrSB\u003e\u003e fBusyStagingBuffers;\n\nA buffer is only ever present in one of the arrays at a time.\n\nWhen we call findStagingBuffer we move a buffer from fAvailableStagingBuffers to fActiveStagingBuffers (or create a new one directly into fActive).\n\nWhen we call unmap during finishFlush all buffers are moved from fActiveStagingBuffers to fBusyStagingBuffers.\n\nWhen the backend sees that a given buffer in fBusyStagingBuffers has finished on the GPU it moves it from fBusyStagingBuffers to fAvailableStagingBuffers.\n\nWith this model we don\u0027t need markAsReady() on GrStagingBuffer and probably not empty() either. Also I your current change I don\u0027t see how you are moving buffers back from fBusyStagingBuffers to fReadyStagingBuffers.",
